enable your deployed UI5 integration card

Enable and configure your UI5 integration card

Enable your deployed UI5 integration card

  1. Access the Administration Console from the user actions dropdown menu under your avatar.

  2. Go to the UI Integration section, expand it, and click Cards.

  3. Search for your card with the key words Latest Sales Orders. You will notice that your project name Latest_Sales_Orders_Card_AC096819U21 is in the card.

    Your card will display under the Uploaded Cards section.

    If you don’t see your deployed card, you may need to refresh the browser.

  4. Click the slider button to enable the card.

The card is now enabled and can be added to the workpage in your workspace.

In this step, for workshops, use your unique identifier ns.Latest_Sales_Orders_Card_AC096819U21.

You can click on Configure to select a different destination for this UI5 integration card. As you used the same S4HANA_ODATA_SalesOrder destination in the target SAP BTP subaccount and also when you developed the card, this step is not required.

Configure the card settings

Before you add the card to your workspace, let’s configure one of the settings of the card.

  1. On the ns.Latest_Sales_Orders_Card_AC096819U21, click Configure.

  2. Under General Settings, change the Maximum Items to 2 and select the destination: S4HANA_ODATA_SalesOrder. Then click Save.

    On the Configure screen, when you click the More settings icon there are more settings that you can configure for the end user.

In the next step you’ll add the card to your workpage in your workspace.
